# Admin loading & a11y

## Loading wrappers need a valid ARIA role

Biome rejects `aria-label` / `aria-busy` on a plain `<div>`. Use `role="status"`:

```tsx
<div role="status" aria-busy="true" aria-label="Loading users">
  <Skeleton ... />
</div>
```

## Skeleton row keys

Do not use array index as React `key`. Use a stable constant:

```tsx
const SKELETON_ROWS = ["a", "b", "c", "d", "e"] as const;
{SKELETON_ROWS.map((id) => (
  <tr key={`users-table-skeleton-${id}`}>...</tr>
))}
```

## Semantic tokens for status pills

Use theme tokens, not hardcoded Tailwind color scales:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
"bg-green-50 text-green-700 dark:bg-green-500/15"

// ✅ GOOD
"bg-primary/10 text-primary"
```

Dialog overlays: `bg-foreground/60`, not `bg-[rgba(...)]`.
